# Pull Request Descriptions

When creating or drafting PR descriptions for this repo:

- Write a **detailed** body with clear sections
- Use **emojis in section headings and bullets** to make the summary scannable
- Prefer short narrative bullets that explain *what* and *why*

## Do not use

- Checkbox / task lists (`- [ ]`, `- [x]`)
- Check-mark style test plans (`✅` / `☐` todo lists)

## Preferred shape

```markdown
## ✨ Summary
- 🧩 What changed and why

## 🛠️ Changes
- 📝 Concrete updates by area

## 🧪 How to verify
- 👀 Manual steps written as normal bullets (not checkboxes)
```
